{"id":"976379a2d99962e1f55c35e4332b4b4de17ad35e","axis":"silent","repo":"grafana/loki","sha":"976379a2d99962e1f55c35e4332b4b4de17ad35e","parsed":{"files":[{"path":"docs/sources/operations/lbac.md","lines":["@@ -0,0 +1,94 @@","+---","+title: Use label-based access control with Loki","+menuTitle: Access control","+description: Describes how to use label-based access control to only query logs that meet specific label requirements.","+aliases:","+weight:","+---","+","+# Use label-based access control with Loki","+","+{{< admonition type=\"note\" >}}","+This feature is experimental and available from v3.7.3. For the latest releases, refer to the [Release notes](https://grafana.com/docs/loki/<LOKI_VERSION>/release-notes/).","+{{< /admonition >}}","+","+Label-based access control (LBAC) restricts the logs a tenant can query to those that match one or more [Prometheus label selectors](https://prometheus.io/docs/prometheus/latest/querying/basics/#time-series-selectors). You associate a set of selectors with a tenant, and queries from that tenant only return data from log streams that match at least one of the selectors. Because the selectors are combined with OR, this corresponds to [disjunctive normal form](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Disjunctive_normal_form), which lets you express any required policy.","+","+LBAC builds on Loki's multi-tenancy: policies are scoped per tenant, so you must run Loki in multi-tenant mode. For more information, refer to the [multi-tenancy](https://grafana.com/docs/loki/<LOKI_VERSION>/operations/multi-tenancy/) documentation.","+","+## Security model","+","+Loki does not include its own authentication layer. Both the tenant (`X-Scope-OrgID`) and the label policy (`X-Prom-Label-Policy`) are read from trusted HTTP headers on incoming requests.","+","+{{< admonition type=\"warning\" >}}","+Never expose the Loki API directly to clients. A client that can reach Loki can set the `X-Scope-OrgID` and `X-Prom-Label-Policy` headers itself and bypass label-based access control entirely. You must run an authentication gateway in front of Loki that authenticates the request, sets the tenant, and attaches the correct label policy.","+{{< /admonition >}}","+","+The gateway is responsible for stripping any user supplied `X-Scope-OrgID` and `X-Prom-Label-Policy` and replacing them with values it derives from the authenticated identity. One open-source gateway that sets these headers is [db-auth-gateway](https://github.com/grafana/db-auth-gateway/). For general guidance on putting an authenticating reverse proxy in front of Loki, refer to the [authentication](https://grafana.com/docs/loki/<LOKI_VERSION>/operations/authentication/) documentation.","+","+## Enable label-based access control","+","+LBAC requires multi-tenant mode, which is the default. Ensure authentication is enabled so that requests carry a tenant:","+","+```yaml","+auth_enabled: true","+```","+","+Then enable LBAC:","+","+```yaml","+lbac:","+  enabled: true","+```","+","+This can also be set with the `-lbac.enabled` command-line flag. When enabled, Loki parses the `X-Prom-Label-Policy` header on incoming requests and enforces the policies it contains.","+","+## Setting up a label policy","+","+A label policy is conveyed to Loki in the `X-Prom-Label-Policy` request header. This header is set by your authentication gateway, not by clients. Each header value has the form:","+","+```","+<tenant>:<URL-encoded selector>","+```","+","+The selector is a standard label matcher set such as `{env=\"dev\"}`, URL-encoded so that it is safe to carry in a header. For example, the policy `{env=\"dev\"}` for tenant `tenant1` is encoded as:","+","+```","+X-Prom-Label-Policy: tenant1:%7Benv%3D%22dev%22%7D","+```","+","+To associate multiple selectors with a tenant, set multiple values. You can either repeat the header or separate the encoded policies with a comma. The selectors are combined with OR: a stream is returned if it matches any one of them.","+","+## Exclude a label","+","+One common use case for an LBAC policy is to exclude logs that have a specific label. For example, to exclude all log lines with the label `secret=true`, use a selector with `secret!=\"true\"`:","+","+```","+{secret!=\"true\"}","+```","+","+## Use multiple selectors","+","+To allow access to both the production and development environments while excluding logs with the label `secret=true` in the production environment, use multiple selectors:","+","+```","+{secret!=\"true\", env=\"prod\"}","+{env=\"dev\"}","+```","+","+These selectors enforce the policy as follows:","+","+* `{secret!=\"true\", env=\"prod\"}` matches and returns log lines from the production environment that do not have the `secret: true` label.","+* `{env=\"dev\"}` matches and returns log lines from the development environment, even if they have the `secret: true` label.","+","+## Label policy scope","+","+Label policies are only applied to the log stream selector of the Loki query. They do not apply to label filter expressions. For more information, refer to the [Log stream selector](https://grafana.com/docs/loki/<LOKI_VERSION>/query/log_queries/#log-stream-selector) and [Label filter expression](https://grafana.com/docs/loki/<LOKI_VERSION>/query/log_queries/#label-filter-expression) sections in the documentation about [Log queries](https://grafana.com/docs/loki/<LOKI_VERSION>/query/log_queries/).","+","+## Writing log lines","+","+Label-based access control is not enforced on write (push) requests. A tenant that is allowed to write can push log lines with any labels, regardless of the label policy that applies to its queries.","+","+## Alertmanager and ruler","+","+Label policies are not enforced by the Alertmanager and ruler. This means that the requests they serve contain everything for a particular tenant without applying label-based access control. For example, listing all rule groups in the ruler returns all rule groups for the tenant, even if a label selector in the policy would exclude some of the labels on the rules."],"additions":94,"deletions":0,"truncated":false},{"path":"docs/sources/shared/configuration.md","lines":["@@ -92,6 +92,11 @@ Pass the `-config.expand-env` flag at the command line to enable this way of set"," # CLI flag: -auth.enabled"," [auth_enabled: <boolean> | default = true]"," ","+lbac:","+  # Enables label based access control through the X-Prom-Label-Policy header.","+  # CLI flag: -lbac.enabled","+  [enabled: <boolean> | default = false]","+"," # The amount of virtual memory in bytes to reserve as ballast in order to"," # optimize garbage collection. Larger ballasts result in fewer garbage"," # collection passes, reducing CPU overhead at the cost of heap size. The ballast"],"additions":5,"deletions":0,"truncated":false},{"path":"integration/client/client.go","lines":["@@ -509,7 +509,7 @@ type Header struct {"," }"," "," // RunRangeQuery runs a 7d query and returns an error if anything went wrong","-// This function is kept to keep backwards copatibility of existing tests.","+// This function is kept to keep backwards compatibility of existing tests."," // Better use (*Client).RunRangeQueryWithStartEnd()"," func (c *Client) RunRangeQuery(ctx context.Context, query string, extraHeaders ...Header) (*Response, error) {"," \tend := c.Now.Add(time.Second)","@@ -673,6 +673,8 @@ func (c *Client) Series(ctx context.Context, matcher string) ([]map[string]strin"," "," \tv := url.Values{}"," \tv.Set(\"match[]\", matcher)","+\tv.Set(\"end\", FormatTS(c.Now.Add(time.Second)))","+\tv.Set(\"start\", FormatTS(c.Now.Add(-7*24*time.Hour)))"," "," \tu, err := url.Parse(c.baseURL)"," \tif err != nil {"],"additions":3,"deletions":1,"truncated":false},{"path":"integration/labelaccess_test.go","lines":["@@ -0,0 +1,476 @@","+//go:build integration","+","+package integration","+","+import (","+\t\"context\"","+\t\"fmt\"","+\t\"net/url\"","+\t\"sort\"","+\t\"strconv\"","+\t\"strings\"","+\t\"testing\"","+\t\"time\"","+","+\t\"github.com/prometheus/prometheus/model/labels\"","+\t\"github.com/prometheus/prometheus/promql/parser\"","+\t\"github.com/stretchr/testify/assert\"","+\t\"github.com/stretchr/testify/require\"","+","+\t\"github.com/grafana/loki/v3/integration/client\"","+\t\"github.com/grafana/loki/v3/integration/cluster\"","+\t\"github.com/grafana/loki/v3/pkg/labelaccess\"","+\t\"github.com/grafana/loki/v3/pkg/labelaccess/types\"","+\t\"github.com/grafana/loki/v3/pkg/util/constants\"","+)","+","+const (","+\tlogsQuery           = `{job=\"varlog\"} |= \"line\"`","+\tmetricsQuery        = \"count_over_time(\" + logsQuery + \" [2h])\"","+\taggregatedLogsQuery = `{__aggregated_metric__=\"varlog_service\"} | logfmt`","+)","+","+func buildLBACPolicyHeaders(tenantID string, policies []types.LabelPolicy) []string {","+\theaders := make([]string, len(policies))","+\tfor i := range policies {","+\t\tmatchers := make([]string, len(policies[i].Selector))","+\t\tfor j, selector := range policies[i].Selector {","+\t\t\tmatcher, err := types.LabelMatcherToPromLabel(selector)","+\t\t\tif err != nil {","+\t\t\t\tpanic(err)","+\t\t\t}","+\t\t\tmatchers[j] = matcher.String()","+\t\t}","+\t\theaders[i] = fmt.Sprintf(\"%s:%s\", tenantID, url.PathEscape(\"{\"+strings.Join(matchers, \", \")+\"}\"))","+\t}","+\treturn headers","+}","+","+// newPolicy builds a LabelPolicy fixture from a selector string, panicking on","+// malformed input.","+func newPolicy(selector string) types.LabelPolicy {","+\tmatchers, err := parser.NewParser(parser.Options{}).ParseMetricSelector(selector)","+\tif err != nil {","+\t\tpanic(err)","+\t}","+\tpolicy := types.LabelPolicy{Selector: make([]*types.LabelMatcher, len(matchers))}","+\tfor i, m := range matchers {","+\t\tlm, err := types.LabelMatcherFromPromLabel(m)","+\t\tif err != nil {","+\t\t\tpanic(err)","+\t\t}","+\t\tpolicy.Selector[i] = lm","+\t}","+\treturn policy","+}","+","+var (","+\ttestCases = []*testQueryAndLabelResults{","+\t\t{","+\t\t\tname:          \"no matches\",","+\t\t\tcreateCluster: clusterAllLBAC,","+\t\t\ttenantID:      randStringRunes(),","+\t\t\tnow:           time.Now(),","+\t\t\tlabelPolicies: []types.LabelPolicy{newPolicy(`{not=\"existing\"}`)},","+\t\t},","+\t\t{","+\t\t\tname:          \"disabled\",","+\t\t\tcreateCluster: clusterAll,","+\t\t\ttenantID:      randStringRunes(),","+\t\t\tnow:           time.Now(),","+\t\t\tlabelPolicies: []types.LabelPolicy{","+\t\t\t\tnewPolicy(`{env=\"dev\"}`),","+\t\t\t},","+\t\t\tlabelValues: map[string][]string{","+\t\t\t\t\"classification\": {\"confidential\", \"secret\"},","+\t\t\t\t\"env\":            {\"dev\", \"prod\"},","+\t\t\t\t\"job\":            {\"varlog\"},","+\t\t\t},","+\t\t\tlines: []string{\"line1\", \"line2\", \"line3\", \"line4\"},","+\t\t\tstreams: []map[string]string{","+\t\t\t\t{","+\t\t\t\t\t\"classification\": \"confidential\",","+\t\t\t\t\t\"env\":            \"dev\",","+\t\t\t\t\t\"job\":            \"varlog\",","+\t\t\t\t},","+\t\t\t\t{","+\t\t\t\t\t\"classification\": \"secret\",","+\t\t\t\t\t\"env\":            \"prod\",","+\t\t\t\t\t\"job\":            \"varlog\",","+\t\t\t\t},","+\t\t\t\t{","+\t\t\t\t\t\"classification\": \"secret\",","+\t\t\t\t\t\"env\":            \"dev\",","+\t\t\t\t\t\"job\":            \"varlog\",","+\t\t\t\t},","+\t\t\t\t{","+\t\t\t\t\t\"job\": \"varlog\",","+\t\t\t\t},","+\t\t\t},","+\t\t},","+\t\t{","+\t\t\tname:          \"lbac enabled\",","+\t\t\tcreateCluster: clusterAllLBAC,","+\t\t\ttenantID:      randStringRunes(),","+\t\t\tnow:           time.Now(),","+\t\t\tlabelPolicies: []types.LabelPolicy{","+\t\t\t\tnewPolicy(`{env=\"dev\"}`),","+\t\t\t},","+\t\t\tlabelValues: map[string][]string{","+\t\t\t\t\"classification\": {\"confidential\", \"secret\"},","+\t\t\t\t\"env\":            {\"dev\"},","+\t\t\t\t\"job\":            {\"varlog\"},","+\t\t\t},","+\t\t\tlines: []string{\"line1\", \"line3\"},","+\t\t\tstreams: []map[string]string{","+\t\t\t\t{","+\t\t\t\t\t\"classification\": \"confidential\",","+\t\t\t\t\t\"env\":            \"dev\",","+\t\t\t\t\t\"job\":            \"varlog\",","+\t\t\t\t},","+\t\t\t\t{","+\t\t\t\t\t\"classification\": \"secret\",","+\t\t\t\t\t\"env\":            \"dev\",","+\t\t\t\t\t\"job\":            \"varlog\",","+\t\t\t\t},","+\t\t\t},","+\t\t},","+\t\t{","+\t\t\tname:          \"multiple policies\",","+\t\t\tcreateCluster: clusterAllLBAC,","+\t\t\ttenantID:      randStringRunes(),","+\t\t\tnow:           time.Now(),","+\t\t\tlabelPolicies: []types.LabelPolicy{","+\t\t\t\tnewPolicy(`{env=\"dev\", classification!=\"secret\"}`),","+\t\t\t\tnewPolicy(`{classification=~\"secre.*\"}`),","+\t\t\t},","+\t\t\tlabelValues: map[string][]string{","+\t\t\t\t\"env\":            {\"dev\", \"prod\"},","+\t\t\t\t\"classification\": {\"secret\", \"confidential\"},","+\t\t\t\t\"job\":            {\"varlog\"},","+\t\t\t},","+\t\t\tlines: []string{\"line1\", \"line3\", \"line4\"},","+\t\t\tstreams: []map[string]string{","+\t\t\t\t{","+\t\t\t\t\t\"classification\": \"confidential\",","+\t\t\t\t\t\"env\":            \"dev\",","+\t\t\t\t\t\"job\":            \"varlog\",","+\t\t\t\t},","+\t\t\t\t{","+\t\t\t\t\t\"classification\": \"secret\",","+\t\t\t\t\t\"env\":            \"dev\",","+\t\t\t\t\t\"job\":            \"varlog\",","+\t\t\t\t},","+\t\t\t\t{","+\t\t\t\t\t\"classification\": \"secret\",","+\t\t\t\t\t\"env\":            \"prod\",","+\t\t\t\t\t\"job\":            \"varlog\",","+\t\t\t\t},","+\t\t\t},","+\t\t},","+\t}","+)","+","+func clusterAll(t *testing.T) *cluster.Component {","+\tclu := cluster.New(nil, cluster.SchemaWithTSDB, func(c *cluster.Cluster) {","+\t\tc.SetSchemaVer(\"v13\")","+\t})","+\tt.Cleanup(func() {","+\t\tassert.NoError(t, clu.Cleanup())","+\t})","+","+\ttAll := clu.AddComponent(\"all\", \"-target=all\")","+\trequire.NoError(t, clu.Run())","+","+\treturn tAll","+}","+","+func clusterAllLBAC(t *testing.T) *cluster.Component {","+\tclu := cluster.New(nil, cluster.SchemaWithTSDB, func(c *cluster.Cluster) {","+\t\tc.SetSchemaVer(\"v13\")","+\t})","+\tt.Cleanup(func() {","+\t\tassert.NoError(t, clu.Cleanup())","+\t})","+","+\ttAll := clu.AddComponent(\"all\", \"-target=all\", \"-lbac.enabled=true\")","+\trequire.NoError(t, clu.Run())","+","+\treturn tAll","+}","+","+func clusterAllLBACAggregation(t *testing.T) *cluster.Component {","+\tclu := cluster.New(nil, cluster.SchemaWithTSDB, func(c *cluster.Cluster) {","+\t\tc.SetSchemaVer(\"v13\")","+\t})","+\tt.Cleanup(func() {","+\t\tassert.NoError(t, clu.Cleanup())","+\t})","+","+\ttAll := clu.AddComponent(\"all\", \"-target=all\", \"-lbac.enabled=true\", \"-limits.aggregation-enabled=true\", \"-pattern-ingester.enabled=true\")","+\trequire.NoError(t, clu.Run())","+","+\treturn tAll","+}","+","+// TestLabelAccessDefault starts a Loki cluster and verifies","+// the query results are as expected as per the testCase configuration","+func TestLabelAccessTestCases(t *testing.T) {","+\tfor _, testCase := range testCases {","+\t\tt.Run(testCase.name, func(t *testing.T) {","+\t\t\tif testCase.createCluster == nil {","+\t\t\t\tpanic(\"test case is missing createCluster function\")","+\t\t\t}","+\t\t\ttAll := testCase.createCluster(t)","+\t\t\ttestCase.ingest(t, tAll)","+\t\t\tcliQuery := testCase.cliQuery(t, tAll)","+","+\t\t\ttestCase.logsQuery(t, cliQuery)","+\t\t\ttestCase.labelValuesQuery(t, cliQuery)","+\t\t\ttestCase.seriesQuery(t, cliQuery)","+\t\t\ttestCase.metricsRangeQuery(t, cliQuery)","+\t\t\ttestCase.metricsQuery(t, cliQuery)","+","+\t\t\ttestCase.flush(t, tAll)","+\t\t\ttestCase.seriesQuery(t, cliQuery)","+\t\t})","+\t}","+}","+","+func TestAggregatedMetricsTestCases(t *testing.T) {","+\tvar aggregatedMetricsTestCases = []*testQueryAndLabelResults{","+\t\t{","+\t\t\tname:          \"aggregated metrics\",","+\t\t\tcreateCluster: clusterAllLBACAggregation,","+\t\t\ttenantID:      randStringRunes(),","+\t\t\tnow:           time.Now(),","+\t\t\tlabelPolicies: []types.LabelPolicy{","+\t\t\t\tnewPolicy(`{env!=\"dev\", classification!=\"secret\"}`),","+\t\t\t\tnewPolicy(`{classification!=\"secret\"}`),","+\t\t\t},","+\t\t\tlabelValues: map[string][]string{","+\t\t\t\t\"job\": {\"varlog\"},","+\t\t\t},","+\t\t\tlines: []string{`ts=1 bytes=1024 count=10 job=\"varlog\" service_name=\"varlog_service\" env=\"dev\" classification=\"confidential\"`,","+\t\t\t\t`ts=4 bytes=8192 count=40 job=\"varlog\" service_name=\"varlog_service\" env=\"prod\" classification=\"notsecret\"`},","+\t\t},","+\t}","+\tfor _, testCase := range aggregatedMetricsTestCases {","+\t\tt.Run(testCase.name, func(t *testing.T) {","+\t\t\tif testCase.createCluster == nil {","+\t\t\t\tpanic(\"test case is missing createCluster function\")","+\t\t\t}","+\t\t\ttAll := testCase.createCluster(t)","+\t\t\ttestCase.ingestAggregatedMetrics(t, tAll)","+","+\t\t\tcliQuery := testCase.cliQuery(t, tAll)","+","+\t\t\ttestCase.aggregatedMetricsQuery(t, cliQuery)","+\t\t\ttestCase.labelValuesQuery(t, cliQuery)","+\t\t})","+\t}","+}","+","+//","+//\t// Query aggregated metrics","+","+//}","+","+type testQueryAndLabelResults struct {","+\tname          string","+\tcreateCluster func(t *testing.T) *cluster.Component","+\ttenantID      string","+\tnow           time.Time","+\tlabelPolicies []types.LabelPolicy","+\tlabelValues   map[string][]string // expected label values that match the label policy","+\tlines         []string            // expected lines that match the label policy","+\tstreams       []map[string]string // expected streams","+}","+","+func (tc *testQueryAndLabelResults) flush(t *testing.T, tAll *cluster.Component) {","+\tcliWrite := client.New(tc.tenantID, \"\", tAll.HTTPURL())","+\trequire.NoError(t, cliWrite.Flush())","+}","+","+func (tc *testQueryAndLabelResults) ingest(t *testing.T, tAll *cluster.Component) *client.Client {","+\tcliWrite := client.New(tc.tenantID, \"\", tAll.HTTPURL())","+\tcliWrite.Now = tc.now","+","+\trequire.NoError(t, cliWrite.PushLogLine(\"line1\", tc.now, nil, map[string]string{\"env\": \"dev\", \"classification\": \"confidential\"}))","+\trequire.NoError(t, cliWrite.PushLogLine(\"line2\", tc.now.Add(time.Second), nil))","+\trequire.NoError(t, cliWrite.PushLogLine(\"line3\", tc.now.Add(2*time.Second), nil, map[string]string{\"classification\": \"secret\", \"env\": \"dev\"}))","+\trequire.NoError(t, cliWrite.PushLogLine(\"line4\", tc.now.Add(3*time.Second), nil, map[string]string{\"classification\": \"secret\", \"env\": \"prod\"}))","+\treturn cliWrite","+}","+","+func (tc *testQueryAndLabelResults) ingestAggregatedMetrics(t *testing.T, tAll *cluster.Component) {","+\tcliWrite := client.New(tc.tenantID, \"\", tAll.HTTPURL())","+\tcliWrite.Now = tc.now","+","+\taggMetricLabels := map[string]string{\"__aggregated_metric__\": \"varlog_service\"}","+","+\t// Aggregated metrics for dev environment with confidential classification","+\trequire.NoError(t, cliWrite.PushLogLine(","+\t\t`ts=1 bytes=1024 count=10 job=\"varlog\" service_name=\"varlog_service\" env=\"dev\" classification=\"confidential\"`,","+\t\ttc.now,","+\t\tnil,","+\t\taggMetricLabels,","+\t))","+","+\t// Aggregated metrics for dev environment with secret classification","+\trequire.NoError(t, cliWrite.PushLogLine(","+\t\t`ts=2 bytes=2048 count=20 job=\"varlog\" service_name=\"varlog_service\" env=\"dev\" classification=\"secret\"`,","+\t\ttc.now.Add(-time.Second),","+\t\tnil,","+\t\taggMetricLabels,","+\t))","+","+\t// Aggregated metrics for prod environment with secret classification","+\trequire.NoError(t, cliWrite.PushLogLine(","+\t\t`ts=3 bytes=4096 count=30 job=\"varlog\" service_name=\"varlog_service\" env=\"prod\" classification=\"secret\"`,","+\t\ttc.now.Add(-2*time.Second),","+\t\tnil,","+\t\taggMetricLabels,","+\t))","+","+\t// Aggregated metrics for prod environment with notsecret classification","+\trequire.NoError(t, cliWrite.PushLogLine(","+\t\t`ts=4 bytes=8192 count=40 job=\"varlog\" service_name=\"varlog_service\" env=\"prod\" classification=\"notsecret\"`,","+\t\ttc.now.Add(-3*time.Second),","+\t\tnil,","+\t\taggMetricLabels,","+\t))","+","+\trequire.NoError(t, cliWrite.Flush())","+}","+","+func (tc *testQueryAndLabelResults) aggregatedMetricsQuery(t *testing.T, qc *client.Client) {","+\tt.Run(\"aggregated-metrics-query\", func(t *testing.T) {","+","+\t\t// query the available lines","+\t\toutput, err := qc.RunRangeQuery(context.Background(), aggregatedLogsQuery,","+\t\t\tclient.Header{Name: \"X-Query-Tags\", Value: \"source=\" + constants.LogsDrilldownAppName})","+\t\trequire.NoError(t, err)","+\t\tassert.Equal(t, \"success\", output.Status)","+\t\tassert.Equal(t, \"streams\", output.Data.ResultType)","+","+\t\tvar actualLines []string","+\t\tfor _, row := range output.Data.Stream {","+\t\t\tfor _, lines := range row.Values {","+\t\t\t\tactualLines = append(actualLines, lines[1])","+\t\t\t}","+\t\t}","+\t\tassert.ElementsMatch(t, tc.lines, actualLines)","+\t})","+}","+","+func (tc *testQueryAndLabelResults) cliQuery(_ *testing.T, tAll *cluster.Component) *client.Client {","+\theaders := buildLBACPolicyHeaders(tc.tenantID, tc.labelPolicies)","+","+\tcliQuery := client.New(","+\t\ttc.tenantID,","+\t\t\"\",","+\t\ttAll.HTTPURL(),","+\t\tclient.InjectHeadersOption{","+\t\t\tlabelaccess.HTTPHeaderKey: headers,","+\t\t},","+\t)","+\tcliQuery.Now = tc.now.Add(4 * time.Second)","+\treturn cliQuery","+}","+","+func (tc *testQueryAndLabelResults) labelValuesQuery(t *testing.T, qc *client.Client) {","+\tt.Run(\"label-values-query\", func(t *testing.T) {","+\t\tlabelMap := make(map[string][]string)","+\t\tlabelNames, err := qc.LabelNames(context.Background())","+\t\trequire.NoError(t, err)","+\t\tfor _, label := range labelNames {","+\t\t\tlabelValues, err := qc.LabelValues(context.Background(), label)","+\t\t\trequire.NoError(t, err)","+\t\t\tlabelMap[label] = labelValues","+\t\t}","+\t\trequire.NoError(t, err)","+","+\t\trequire.Equal(t, normalizeLabelsData(tc.labelValues), normalizeLabelsData(labelMap))","+\t})","+}","+func (tc *testQueryAndLabelResults) logsQuery(t *testing.T, qc *client.Client) {","+\tt.Run(\"logs-query\", func(t *testing.T) {","+","+\t\t// query the available lines","+\t\toutput, err := qc.RunRangeQuery(context.Background(), logsQuery)","+\t\trequire.NoError(t, err)","+\t\tassert.Equal(t, \"success\", output.Status)","+\t\tassert.Equal(t, \"streams\", output.Data.ResultType)","+","+\t\tvar actualLines []string","+\t\tfor _, row := range output.Data.Stream {","+\t\t\tfor _, lines := range row.Values {","+\t\t\t\tactualLines = append(actualLines, lines[1])","+\t\t\t}","+\t\t}","+\t\tassert.ElementsMatch(t, tc.lines, actualLines)","+\t})","+}","+","+func (tc *testQueryAndLabelResults) seriesQuery(t *testing.T, qc *client.Client) {","+\tt.Run(\"series-query\", func(t *testing.T) {","+\t\tseriesResult, err := qc.Series(context.Background(), \"{}\")","+\t\trequire.NoError(t, err)","+\t\trequire.ElementsMatch(t, tc.streams, seriesResult)","+\t})","+}","+","+func (tc *testQueryAndLabelResults) metricsQuery(t *testing.T, qc *client.Client) {","+\tt.Run(\"metrics-query\", func(t *testing.T) {","+\t\toutput, err := qc.RunQuery(context.Background(), metricsQuery)","+\t\trequire.NoError(t, err)","+\t\tassert.Equal(t, \"success\", output.Status)","+\t\tassert.Equal(t, \"vector\", output.Data.ResultType)","+","+\t\tvar streams []map[string]string","+\t\tfor _, row := range output.Data.Vector {","+\t\t\tstreams = append(streams, labels.FromMap(row.Metric).Map())","+\t\t}","+\t\tassert.ElementsMatch(t, tc.streams, streams)","+\t})","+}","+","+func (tc *testQueryAndLabelResults) metricsRangeQuery(t *testing.T, qc *client.Client) {","+\tt.Run(\"metrics-range-query\", func(t *testing.T) {","+\t\toutput, err := qc.RunRangeQuery(context.Background(), metricsQuery)","+\t\trequire.NoError(t, err)","+\t\trequire.Equal(t, \"success\", output.Status)","+\t\trequire.Equal(t, \"matrix\", output.Data.ResultType)","+\t\trequire.EqualValues(t, len(tc.lines), sumMatrixValues(t, output.Data.Matrix))","+\t})","+}","+","+func sumMatrixValues(t *testing.T, matrix []client.MatrixValues) float64 {","+\tt.Helper()","+","+\tvar total float64","+\tfor _, row := range matrix {","+\t\tfor _, sample := range row.Values {","+\t\t\trequire.Len(t, sample, 2)","+\t\t\tvalue, ok := sample[1].(string)","+\t\t\trequire.True(t, ok)","+","+\t\t\tparsed, err := strconv.ParseFloat(value, 64)","+\t\t\trequire.NoError(t, err)","+\t\t\ttotal += parsed","+\t\t}","+\t}","+","+\treturn total","+}","+","+func normalizeLabelsData(labels map[string][]string) map[string][]string {","+\tnormalized := make(map[string][]string, len(labels))","+\tfor name, values := range labels {","+\t\tsortedValues := append([]string(nil), values...)","+\t\tsort.Strings(sortedValues)","+\t\tnormalized[name] = sortedValues","+\t}","+\treturn normalized","+}"],"additions":476,"deletions":0,"truncated":false},{"path":"integration/multi_tenant_queries_test.go","lines":["@@ -16,10 +16,12 @@ import ("," "," func TestMultiTenantQuery(t *testing.T) {"," \tt.Skip(\"This test is flaky on CI but it's hardly reproducible locally.\")","-\tclu := cluster.New(nil)","-\tdefer func() {","+\tclu := cluster.New(nil, cluster.SchemaWithTSDB, func(c *cluster.Cluster) {","+\t\tc.SetSchemaVer(\"v13\")","+\t})","+\tt.Cleanup(func() {"," \t\tassert.NoError(t, clu.Cleanup())","-\t}()","+\t})"," "," \tvar ("," \t\ttAll = clu.AddComponent("],"additions":5,"deletions":3,"truncated":false},{"path":"integration/shared_test.go","lines":["@@ -7,11 +7,7 @@ import ("," \t\"time\""," )"," ","-var randomGenerator *rand.Rand","-","-func init() {","-\trandomGenerator = rand.New(rand.NewSource(time.Now().UnixNano()))","-}","+var randomGenerator = rand.New(rand.NewSource(time.Now().UnixNano()))"," "," var letterRunes = []rune(\"abcdefghijklmnopqrstuvwxyzABCDEFGHIJKLMNOPQRSTUVWXYZ\")"," "],"additions":1,"deletions":5,"truncated":false},{"path":"pkg/labelaccess/aggregated_metrics.go","lines":["@@ -0,0 +1,278 @@","+package labelaccess","+","+import (","+\t\"errors\"","+\t\"fmt\"","+\t\"net/http\"","+\t\"strings\"","+","+\t\"github.com/go-kit/log/level\"","+\t\"github.com/prometheus/prometheus/model/labels\"","+","+\t\"github.com/grafana/loki/v3/pkg/labelaccess/types\"","+\tlogql_log \"github.com/grafana/loki/v3/pkg/logql/log\"","+\t\"github.com/grafana/loki/v3/pkg/logql/syntax\"","+\t\"github.com/grafana/loki/v3/pkg/util/constants\"","+\tutil_log \"github.com/grafana/loki/v3/pkg/util/log\"","+)","+","+// isQueryRequest checks if the request is a Loki query","+func isQueryRequest(r *http.Request) bool {","+\tpath := r.URL.Path","+\tisQuery := strings.Contains(path, \"/loki/api/v1/query\") ||","+\t\tstrings.Contains(path, \"/loki/api/v1/query_range\")","+","+\treturn isQuery","+}","+","+// ModifyAggregatedMetricsQuery modifies Loki queries for aggregated metrics","+// to include label-based access control (LBAC) filters.","+//","+// For aggregated metrics, labels are stored inside the log content rather than","+// as stream labels, so we need to apply LBAC filters after parsing the log content","+// with the logfmt parser. This function:","+//  1. Identifies queries targeting aggregated metrics","+//  2. Extracts LBAC policies for the tenant","+//  3. Builds filter expressions combining all policies (ORed together)","+//  4. Injects a logfmt parser and label filter into the FRONT of query pipeline","+//  5. Updates the request URL with the modified query","+//","+// The resulting query will contain a pipeline that parses log lines with logfmt","+// and filters out lines that don't match the LBAC policies, ensuring that","+// users only see aggregated metrics they have permission to access.","+func ModifyAggregatedMetricsQuery(r *http.Request, matchers LabelPolicySet) error {","+\t// Get the query parameter","+\tquery := r.URL.Query().Get(\"query\")","+\tif query == \"\" {","+\t\treturn nil","+\t}","+","+\t// Extract the OrgID from the request","+\torgID := r.Header.Get(\"X-Scope-OrgID\")","+\tif orgID == \"\" {","+\t\treturn nil","+\t}","+","+\t// Get the policies for this tenant","+\tpolicies, exists := matchers[orgID]","+\tif !exists || len(policies) == 0 {","+\t\treturn nil","+\t}","+","+\t// Build filter expressions for each policy","+\tpolicyFilterer, err := buildPolicyFilter(policies)","+\tif err != nil {","+\t\treturn err","+\t}","+","+\tlogfmtParser := syntax.MultiStageExpr{","+\t\t&syntax.LogfmtParserExpr{},","+\t\t&syntax.LabelFilterExpr{","+\t\t\tLabelFilterer: policyFilterer,","+\t\t},","+\t}","+","+\t// Parse the original query using the LogQL parser","+\texpr, err := syntax.ParseExpr(query)","+\tif err != nil {","+\t\t_ = level.Error(util_log.Logger).Log(","+\t\t\t\"msg\", \"failed to parse aggregated metrics query\",","+\t\t\t\"query\", query,","+\t\t\t\"error\", err,","+\t\t)","+\t\treturn err","+\t}","+","+\t// Check if this is a query for aggregated metrics streams","+\tif !isAggregatedMetricQueryString(expr) {","+\t\treturn nil","+\t}","+","+\tvar modifiedQuery string","+\tswitch e := expr.(type) {","+\tcase syntax.SampleExpr:","+\t\t// For sample expressions (metric queries), we need to identify the log selector","+\t\t// and add our filter to that part before any range operations","+\t\tmodifiedQuery, err = modifySampleExpr(e, logfmtParser)","+\t\tif err != nil {","+\t\t\treturn err","+\t\t}","+\tcase syntax.LogSelectorExpr:","+\t\tmodifiedQuery, err = modifyLogSelectorExpr(e, logfmtParser)","+\t\tif err != nil {","+\t\t\treturn err","+\t\t}","+\t}","+","+\tif modifiedQuery != \"\" && modifiedQuery != query {","+\t\t// Update the query parameter","+\t\tq := r.URL.Query()","+\t\tq.Set(\"query\", modifiedQuery)","+\t\tr.URL.RawQuery = q.Encode()","+","+\t\t_ = level.Info(util_log.Logger).Log(","+\t\t\t\"msg\", \"modified query for aggregated metrics to respect LBAC\",","+\t\t\t\"original\", query,","+\t\t\t\"modified\", modifiedQuery,","+\t\t\t\"orgID\", orgID,","+\t\t\t\"policyCount\", len(policies),","+\t\t)","+\t}","+","+\treturn nil","+}","+","+func prependPipelineExpr(e *syntax.PipelineExpr, logfmtParser syntax.MultiStageExpr) (*syntax.PipelineExpr, error) {","+\te.MultiStages = append(logfmtParser, e.MultiStages...)","+\treturn e, nil","+}","+","+// findRangeAggregationExpr attempts to find a RangeAggregationExpr within a SampleExpr","+// This helps us locate where to insert our filter in complex metric queries","+func findRangeAggregationExpr(expr syntax.SampleExpr) (*syntax.RangeAggregationExpr, bool) {","+\tswitch e := expr.(type) {","+\tcase *syntax.RangeAggregationExpr:","+\t\treturn e, true","+\tcase *syntax.VectorAggregationExpr:","+\t\treturn findRangeAggregationExpr(e.Left)","+\tdefault:","+\t\treturn nil, false","+\t}","+}","+","+// isAggregatedMetricQueryString checks if a query string targets aggregated metrics","+func isAggregatedMetricQueryString(expr syntax.Expr) bool {","+\tvar matchers []*labels.Matcher","+\tswitch e := expr.(type) {","+\tcase syntax.SampleExpr:","+\t\tselector, err := e.Selector()","+\t\tif err != nil {","+\t\t\treturn false","+\t\t}","+","+\t\tmatchers = selector.Matchers()","+\tcase syntax.LogSelectorExpr:","+\t\tmatchers = e.Matchers()","+\tdefault:","+\t\treturn false","+\t}","+","+\tif len(matchers) == 0 {","+\t\treturn false","+\t}","+","+\tfor _, matcher := range matchers {","+\t\tif matcher.Name == constants.AggregatedMetricLabel {","+\t\t\treturn true","+\t\t}","+\t}","+","+\treturn false","+}","+","+// modifySampleExpr modifies a SampleExpr to add LBAC filtering via a logfmt parser","+// This is used for metric queries based on aggregated metrics","+func modifySampleExpr(expr syntax.SampleExpr, logfmtParser syntax.MultiStageExpr) (string, error) {","+\trangeExpr, ok := findRangeAggregationExpr(expr)","+\tif !ok {","+\t\treturn \"\", fmt.Errorf(\"unsupported aggregated metric expression\")","+\t}","+","+\t// Extract the log selector from the range expression","+\tlogSelector, err := rangeExpr.Selector()","+\tif err != nil {","+\t\treturn \"\", err","+\t}","+","+\t// Create a new pipeline expression with our modified pipeline","+\tvar pipelineExpr *syntax.PipelineExpr","+","+\tif existingPipeline, ok := logSelector.(*syntax.PipelineExpr); ok {","+\t\t// If there's already a pipeline, prepend our stages","+\t\tpipelineExpr, err = prependPipelineExpr(existingPipeline, logfmtParser)","+\t\tif err != nil {","+\t\t\treturn \"\", err","+\t\t}","+\t} else if matchersExpr, ok := logSelector.(*syntax.MatchersExpr); ok {","+\t\t// If it's just matchers, create a new pipeline","+\t\tpipelineExpr = &syntax.PipelineExpr{","+\t\t\tLeft:        matchersExpr,","+\t\t\tMultiStages: logfmtParser,","+\t\t}","+\t} else {","+\t\treturn \"\", fmt.Errorf(\"unsupported log selector type %T\", logSelector)","+\t}","+","+\t// Update the log selector in the range expression","+\tif pipelineExpr != nil {","+\t\trangeExpr.Left.Left = pipelineExpr","+\t}","+","+\treturn expr.String(), nil","+}","+","+// modifyLogSelectorExpr modifies a LogSelectorExpr to add LBAC filtering via a logfmt parser","+// This is used for log queries of aggregated metrics","+func modifyLogSelectorExpr(expr syntax.LogSelectorExpr, logfmtParser syntax.MultiStageExpr) (string, error) {","+\tvar pipelineExpr syntax.LogSelectorExpr","+","+\tswitch e := expr.(type) {","+\tcase *syntax.MatchersExpr:","+\t\tpipelineExpr = &syntax.PipelineExpr{","+\t\t\tLeft:        e,","+\t\t\tMultiStages: logfmtParser,","+\t\t}","+\tcase *syntax.PipelineExpr:","+\t\tvar err error","+\t\tpipelineExpr, err = prependPipelineExpr(e, logfmtParser)","+\t\tif err != nil {","+\t\t\treturn \"\", err","+\t\t}","+\tdefault:","+\t\t_ = level.Error(util_log.Logger).Log(","+\t\t\t\"msg\", \"unexpected LogSelectorExpr type\",","+\t\t\t\"type\", fmt.Sprintf(\"%T\", e),"],"additions":234,"deletions":0,"truncated":false}],"additions":818,"deletions":9,"truncated":true,"file_count":7},"error":null,"fetched_at":"2026-07-01T11:09:53.084332+00:00"}